	env := new(mock.Environment)
	env.On("Pwd").Return(tmpDir)
```","created_at":"2026-03-03T06:43:27Z","id":2876423366,"in_reply_to_id":null,"line":21,"path":"src/config/segment_cache_test.go","user":"Copilot"}
{"body":"In `restoreCache`, assigning `segment.writer = v` replaces the writer instance that was just initialized in `MapSegmentWithWriter`, which drops runtime state held in unexported fields (notably `env`/`options` in `segments.Base`). Cached writers restored this way can panic or behave incorrectly when templates call methods that rely on `env`/`options` (e.g. `Scm.RelativeDir()` uses `s.env.Pwd()`). Instead of replacing the writer, copy the cached state into the already-initialized writer (same idea as the previous JSON unmarshal approach), so the initialized `env`/`options` remain intact.","created_at":"2026-06-24T10:16:20Z","id":3466293968,"in_reply_to_id":null,"line":328,"path":"src/config/segment.go","user":"Copilot"}
