{"body":"This test overwrites the global `template.Cache` but never restores it, which can leak state into other tests in the `config` package depending on execution order. Save the previous value and restore it in a defer to keep tests isolated.","created_at":"2026-06-24T10:16:21Z","id":3466294047,"in_reply_to_id":null,"line":18,"path":"src/config/segment_cache_test.go","user":"Copilot"}
{"body":"The test currently validates that cached writers round-trip, but it doesn’t cover the important case where restored writers must retain initialized runtime state (e.g. `env`/`options` inside `segments.Base`). Without that, cached writers can panic when templates call methods that use `env`. Add an assertion using a segment whose `Enabled()` accesses `env` (e.g. `root`) to ensure restore keeps the initialized writer instance intact.","created_at":"2026-06-24T10:16:21Z","id":3466294070,"in_reply_to_id":null,"line":65,"path":"src/config/segment_cache_test.go","user":"Copilot"}

